- Is he gonna be okay?

72
00:03:29,034 --> 00:03:30,340
- Yeah, just come with me.

73
00:03:30,384 --> 00:03:31,689
- Nuh-uh.
I'm going in with him.

74
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:33,213
- I need you to stay here.

75
00:03:33,256 --> 00:03:35,389
- Just tell me plain.
Is my dad gonna be okay?

76
00:03:35,432 --> 00:03:37,521
- You watched over my daughter,

77
00:03:37,565 --> 00:03:40,524
and we're gonna
watch over your dad.

78
00:03:40,568 --> 00:03:41,743
Okay?

79
00:03:45,747 --> 00:03:48,706
- First, I divide the pleura
to isolate the diaphragm.

80
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:51,535
Then, with forceps
applying gentle traction,

81
00:03:51,579 --> 00:03:54,016
I plicate the paralyzed area
using a series of U-sutures.

82
00:03:54,059 --> 00:03:55,322
- Where are those anchored?

83
00:03:55,365 --> 00:03:57,324
- Costal arch of the sixth rib.

84
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:58,629
I also dug deep and found

85
00:03:58,673 --> 00:04:01,284
a completely
endoscopic approach.

86
00:04:01,328 --> 00:04:03,547
- No partial thoracotomy?

87
00:04:03,591 --> 00:04:05,549
Since when?
That's not how I trained.

88
00:04:05,593 --> 00:04:07,290
- You got some reading to do.

89
00:04:08,596 --> 00:04:10,598
- Damn, Duke,
you're putting me on the ropes.

90
00:04:14,384 --> 00:04:16,995
- I'm just, I'm so mad
at myself right now.

91
00:04:17,039 --> 00:04:18,606
- So much
for telling you my news.

92
00:04:18,649 --> 00:04:21,348
- We have four children
under 10 already.

93
00:04:21,391 --> 00:04:22,566
But, no,
I have to suggest to Martin

94
00:04:22,610 --> 00:04:24,568
that we adopt another one.
Why?

95
00:04:24,612 --> 00:04:27,571
What am I doing?
Why do I always do this?

96
00:04:27,615 --> 00:04:29,617
But it's like if you see
a squirrel in the park

97
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,575
