a pigeon with a bum wing

98
00:04:31,619 --> 00:04:32,576
or whatever,
do you not try to rescue it?

99
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,012
- No.

100
00:04:34,056 --> 00:04:35,449
- You don't?
I do.

101
00:04:35,492 --> 00:04:38,278
That's, like, my go-to.
I just can't help myself.

102
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:40,367
But Martin, you know,
you should've seen the look

103
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:42,586
on his face this morning,
Vijay, it was like...

104
00:04:42,630 --> 00:04:44,414
I don't know.
What's a word that means angry

105
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:46,329
but also profoundly
exasperated?

106
00:04:46,373 --> 00:04:47,591
- English is not my first
language, but--

107
00:04:47,635 --> 00:04:50,333
- I see these kids
in the refugee camps,

108
00:04:50,377 --> 00:04:51,465
and I see the looks
on their faces,

109
00:04:51,508 --> 00:04:53,336
and it's a no-brainer for me.

110
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:56,774
We have money, we have space,
we--Martin--ugh, Martin.

111
00:04:56,818 --> 00:04:58,341
No, Martin's right.
Martin's right.

112
00:04:58,385 --> 00:05:00,343
Martin is always right.

113
00:05:00,387 --> 00:05:01,649
We have a full family as is,

114
00:05:01,692 --> 00:05:02,650
and there are tons
of other ways to help.

115
00:05:02,693 --> 00:05:04,434
Thank you.

116
00:05:04,478 --> 00:05:06,044
Thank you for talking
me through this, Vijay.

117
00:05:06,088 --> 00:05:08,569
I appreciate it.
Now hit me with the good news.

118
00:05:08,612 --> 00:05:09,744
What's going on?

119
00:05:09,787 --> 00:05:11,746
- We are having a baby.

120
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,792
- What?

121
00:05:14,836 --> 00:05:17,099
Are you seeing someone?

122
00:05:17,142 --> 00:05:19,580
- Not me, but Ella,
she's carrying my grandchild.

123
00:05:19,623 --> 00:05:21,799
Can you believe it?

124
00:05:21,843 --> 00:05:22,800
- No, not even a little bit.

125
00:05:22,844 --> 00:05:24,541
- At first, it was all bad,

126
00:05:24,585 --> 00:05:27,457
but what choice do I have
but to take it as a blessing?

127
00:05:27,501 --> 00:05:29,720
I can't stop smiling.

128
00:05:34,725 --> 00:05:36,640
Are you okay?

129
00:05:36,684 --> 00:05:38,512
- We're having a baby.

130
00:05:38,555 --> 00:05:40,427
We're having a baby!

131
00:05:49,827 --> 00:05:51,438
- Maybe you're not
stretching it enough.

132
00:05:51,481 --> 00:05:53,396
- You know what?
I never thought of that.

133
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,833
- Really?
- No, not really.

134
00:05:55,877 --> 00:05:58,488
I am doing all
of the recommended stretches

135
00:05:58,532 --> 00:06:00,664
and exercises,
and you know what?

136
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:02,405
Sometimes things just hurt.

137
00:06:02,449 --> 00:06:04,842
- On a scale of one to ten,
how's your pain level?

138
00:06:04,886 --> 00:06:05,887
- A hard one.

139
00:06:05,930 --> 00:06:07,105
- Sounds more like...

140
00:06:07,149 --> 00:06:08,542
- Oh, you got me.

141
00:06:08,585 --> 00:06:11,109
Yeah, my pain level
is jazz hands.

142
00:06:11,153 --> 00:06:12,850
You know what?
even if you are right,

143
00:06:12,894 --> 00:06:15,853
and I am in otherworldly pain,

144
00:06:15,897 --> 00:06:18,508
I've got physical therapy
right after work.

145
00:06:18,552 --> 00:06:20,510
- That's in nine hours.
Why don't you see if Ligon

146
00:06:20,554 --> 00:06:22,120
can squeeze you in
for a quick session?

147
00:06:22,164 --> 00:06:23,426
Just so you can
get through the day.

148
00:06:23,470 --> 00:06:24,514
Hm?

149
00:06:39,921 --> 00:06:41,444
- What's wrong?

150
00:06:41,488 --> 00:06:43,185
- This time,
I should be on top.

151
00:06:45,709 --> 00:06:48,538
- I, of course, say that
from a therapeutic standpoint.

152
00:06:50,975 --> 00:06:52,412
- Ms. Richards.

153
00:06:52,455 --> 00:06:53,717
Welcome to New Amsterdam.

154
00:06:53,761 --> 00:06:55,719
- Thrilled to be here.

155
00:06:55,763 --> 00:06:58,505
- Yeah, so I understand
that you were previously

156
00:06:58,548 --> 00:07:00,724
at Mount Zion under Dr. Castro.

157
00:07:00,768 --> 00:07:03,205
- Yes.
I'm embarrassed to ask you,

158
00:07:03,248 --> 00:07:06,730
but would mind?

159
00:07:06,774 --> 00:07:10,168
Could you just write,
"Warm regards, Molly?"

160
00:07:10,212 --> 00:07:11,866
- Of course.

161
00:07:11,909 --> 00:07:13,955
- It's an old co-worker.

162
00:07:13,998 --> 00:07:17,915
We recently
lost a mutual friend.

163
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:19,787
I can't grip the--ow.

164
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:21,832
- It's not a problem.
There you go.

165
00:07:21,876 --> 00:07:23,443
- Thank you, dear.

166
00:07:23,486 --> 00:07:25,749
- I'm Dr. Sharpe.
I run the oncology--

167
00:07:25,793 --> 00:07:30,450
Dr. Castro and I
head the department.

168
00:07:30,493 --> 00:07:33,714
- I'm glad to see women
are running things here, too.

169
00:07:33,757 --> 00:07:37,587
I was a partner
at Goldman and Fitch.

170
00:07:37,631 --> 00:07:40,198
- Investment banking
Impressive.

171
00:07:40,242 --> 00:07:41,765
I have a number
of patients in that field.

172
00:07:41,809 --> 00:07:43,767
Almost all are men.

173
00:07:43,811 --> 00:07:48,250
- We gals, as they called us,
were about one in ten.

174
00:07:48,293 --> 00:07:50,861
It was great fun,
before I was sidelined

175
00:07:50,905 --> 00:07:52,559
by this stupid disease.

176
00:07:52,602 --> 00:07:54,691
- I can see
you're in a lot of pain.

177
00:07:54,735 --> 00:07:56,780
- Dr. Castro warned me
this latest

178
00:07:56,824 --> 00:08:01,002
experimental agent
might be rough.

179
00:08:01,045 --> 00:08:03,961
- How many have you tried?

180
00:08:04,005 --> 00:08:05,920
- I don't know.
Seven.

181
00:08:10,011 --> 00:08:11,621
- How you feeling?

182
00:08:11,665 --> 00:08:13,536
I was gonna make
a Floyd Mayweather reference,

183
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:14,972
but I don't think
sports is your thing.

184
00:08:15,016 --> 00:08:16,670
- He was a boxer.

185
00:08:16,713 --> 00:08:18,759
- Oh, was he?
Thank you for that.

186
00:08:18,802 --> 00:08:21,979
Uh, Marquis, you have a heart
that's been working overtime.

187
00:08:22,023 --> 00:08:23,807
Do you know
you have hypertension?

188
00:08:23,851 --> 00:08:24,808
- Of course
my blood pressure's up.

189
00:08:24,852 --> 00:08:26,549
I'm in the damn hospital.

190
00:08:26,593 --> 00:08:28,246
You get me outside,
it's a different story.

191
00:08:28,290 --> 00:08:29,683
- Well,
it's high blood pressure

192
00:08:29,726 --> 00:08:30,684
that brought you in here.

193
00:08:30,727 --> 00:08:31,989
- That's impossible.

194
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,991
I exercise every day.
I eat healthy.

195
00:08:34,035 --> 00:08:35,863
- Your condition's been
developing for some time.

196
00:08:35,906 --> 00:08:38,039
When's the last time you that
had a checkup or a physical?

197
00:08:38,082 --> 00:08:39,736
- Not since I've been alive.

198
00:08:39,780 --> 00:08:42,652
- Why go to the doctor
when you're healthy?

199
00:08:42,696 --> 00:08:44,785
- Best time to go to the doctor
is before you get sick.

200
00:08:44,828 --> 00:08:46,526
Blood sugar checks,
cancer screenings--

201
00:08:46,569 --> 00:08:48,702
- And the added benefit
of missing work?

202
00:08:50,617 --> 00:08:52,009
- How many guys I met today

203
00:08:52,053 --> 00:08:53,794
have the same policy
on doctors?

204
00:08:55,056 --> 00:08:56,057
- All of them.

205
00:09:07,329 --> 00:09:08,286
- Hi, there.

206
00:09:08,330 --> 00:09:09,766
- Stroller guy.

207
00:09:09,810 --> 00:09:12,856
- Yeah.
Also known as Dr. Max Goodwin.

208
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,031
- Dr. G.

209
00:09:14,075 --> 00:09:15,293
- That's cooler.
Let's go with that.

210
00:09:15,337 --> 00:09:16,904
- Kenny.

211
00:09:16,947 --> 00:09:17,905
Thanks for helping
my boy Quis out.

212
00:09:17,948 --> 00:09:18,906
- Sure.

213
00:09:18,949 --> 00:09:20,603
- How's he doing?

214
00:09:20,647 --> 00:09:23,301
- It's tough to say,
but just glad I was there.

215
00:09:23,345 --> 00:09:25,303
- Marquis is one
of my best customers.

216
00:09:25,347 --> 00:09:27,044
How about I give you
a trim free of charge?

217
00:09:27,088 --> 00:09:28,742
- You know what?
I actually...

218
00:09:28,785 --> 00:09:31,048
I have a free service for you.

219
00:09:31,092 --> 00:09:32,659
- What kind of service?

220
00:09:34,704 --> 00:09:35,836
- What do you think
about Kenny's Kuts

221
00:09:35,879 --> 00:09:38,099
having its own
in-house physician?

222
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:45,889
- So you want to set up
in my shop?

223
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:47,499
- Uh, yeah.

224
00:09:47,543 --> 00:09:48,631
I want to give consultations
to your customers,

225
00:09:48,675 --> 00:09:50,328
free of charge.

226
00:09:50,372 --> 00:09:52,287
- Yeah, but, like, here?
Like, inside the shop?

227
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:53,331
- Right here.

228
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:54,637
- Look, Doc, the only cutting

229
00:09:54,681 --> 00:09:57,640
that goes on inside
this clinic is hair.

230
00:09:57,684 --> 00:09:59,468
- Look, Marquis
is your customer, right?

231
00:09:59,511 --> 00:10:02,645
He just had a cardiac emergency
due to unchecked hypertension.

232
00:10:02,689 --> 00:10:05,430
But what if he had a doctor
checking his blood pressure

233
00:10:05,474 --> 00:10:07,868
every so often, say,
every time he gets a haircut?

234
00:10:07,911 --> 00:10:09,173
- I feel you,
but what makes you think

235
00:10:09,217 --> 00:10:10,566
all of my customers need help?

236
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,134
- Three in four African
American men develop

237
00:10:13,177 --> 00:10:14,875
high blood pressure
by the age of 55,

238
00:10:14,918 --> 00:10:20,315
and are twice as likely
to die from cardiac disease.

239
00:10:20,358 --> 00:10:22,665
- I don't know, man.
Not buying it.

240
00:10:22,709 --> 00:10:25,276
- Look, it's not gonna
cost you a thing, all right?

241
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,669
Once a week,
I'll spend an hour in the back,

242
00:10:26,713 --> 00:10:28,410
and if anybody wants

243
00:10:28,453 --> 00:10:30,325
to get their blood pressure
checked, I'm here.

244
00:10:30,368 --> 00:10:32,457
And if it's high,
I give them a pill.

245
00:10:32,501 --> 00:10:34,198
- What you think, man?

246
00:10:34,242 --> 00:10:35,504
- I don't know.

247
00:10:35,547 --> 00:10:39,160
White guy in the back,
handing out pills?

248
00:10:39,203 --> 00:10:40,683
That doesn't look too good.

249
00:10:42,729 --> 00:10:44,382
- What's in it for you?

250
00:10:44,426 --> 00:10:46,515
- I won't have to watch
another 14-year-old girl

251
00:10:46,558 --> 00:10:48,299
think her dad just died.

252
